          <h2>Lifting Working Group </h2>
          <p>Injuries arising from lifting operations  account for a significant proportion of the total of those occurring offshore;  typically about 20%.&nbsp; In response, the  IRF Lifting Working Group has formulated a regulatory strategy to address  worldwide lifting operations.&nbsp; The  strategy is due for implementation during 2007 and includes: </p>
          <ol type="a">
            <li> Inspection templates addressing:  Planning of lifting operations, Competency assurance, Maintenance, and Man  riding using winches.</li>
            <li> Recording of the root causes of  investigated incidents using a standardised methodology (Human, Technology,  Organisation) and</li>
            <li> A central database to collate worldwide  regulatory inspection and incident data.&nbsp;  Reports of the findings derived from the database will be published on  the IRF web site.&nbsp; <br />
              For further information contact <a href="mailto:iain.paterson@hse.gsi.gov.uk">iain.paterson@hse.gsi.gov.uk</a>
            </li>
